WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.507 --> 00:00:09.801
[indistinct announcement
over P.A. system]

2
00:00:09.843 --> 00:00:11.886
- Robby.
- Yep.

3
00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:14.014
- Cellulitis
on the dorsum of the foot.

4
00:00:14.097 --> 00:00:16.016
now spreading up the leg.

5
00:00:16.099 --> 00:00:17.225
- Hello. I'm Dr. Robby.

6
00:00:17.308 --> 00:00:18.977
Mind if I take a look?

7
00:00:19.019 --> 00:00:21.021
- How long do you think
this is gonna take?

8
00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:22.647
I took an early lunch break.

9
00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:23.773
[gasps]

10
00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:24.983
- I don't know
that you're gonna

11
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:26.860
make it back to work today.

12
00:00:26.901 --> 00:00:28.528
Erythema and warmth
halfway up her knee.

13
00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:29.654
When did you see her. Donnie?

14
00:00:29.696 --> 00:00:32.115
- He didn't. I did.

15
00:00:32.198 --> 00:00:33.616
- When?
- About four hours ago.

16
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:35.035
Gave her a dose of Keflex.

17
00:00:35.076 --> 00:00:36.536
told her to come back
if things got worse.

18
00:00:36.619 --> 00:00:38.538
- Things have
definitely gotten worse.

19
00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:39.539
Dana. what's open?

20
00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:40.999
- Trauma Two.

21
00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:42.500
- Jesse. can you get her
started in Trauma Two

22
00:00:42.542 --> 00:00:43.752
with some vanco
and blood cultures. please?

23
00:00:43.835 --> 00:00:45.211
- Got it. boss.
- I'm coming with.

24
00:00:45.295 --> 00:00:47.338
- Suit yourself.

25
00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:50.592
- Santos. you want in
on Trauma Two?

26
00:00:50.675 --> 00:00:53.553
- Too much charting.
too little time.

27
00:00:53.636 --> 00:00:57.348
62-year-old male presents
with chief complaint

28
00:00:57.390 --> 00:00:58.516
of left lower back pain.

29
00:00:58.558 --> 00:00:59.976
Considered the diagnosis--
- Hey.

30
00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:01.186
- Oh. Jesus Christ.

31
00:01:01.227 --> 00:01:02.645
I'm charting.

32
00:01:02.729 --> 00:01:04.147
- Sorry.

33
00:01:04.230 --> 00:01:05.148
[sighs]

34
00:01:05.231 --> 00:01:06.733
Did I do something wrong?

35
00:01:06.775 --> 00:01:08.485
- Besides interrupting me?
Probably.

36
00:01:08.568 --> 00:01:10.070
- Then I apologize.

37
00:01:10.153 --> 00:01:13.740
I know that second year
of residency can be stressful.

38
00:01:13.782 --> 00:01:16.910
so if there's anything
I can do to help you...

39
00:01:16.993 --> 00:01:18.203
like stop talking.

40
00:01:18.244 --> 00:01:20.538
- That's a great idea.
- Yeah.

41
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:24.709
- Considered the diagnosis of
aortic aneurysm or dissection.

42
00:01:24.751 --> 00:01:26.419
- Got a new one for you in 13.

43
00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:29.047
- I'm 20 charts behind.
and the new attending

44
00:01:29.089 --> 00:01:30.215
is threatening
to make me repeat

45
00:01:30.256 --> 00:01:31.341
a year if I can't catch up.

46
00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:32.592
- Cry me a river.

47
00:01:32.634 --> 00:01:33.718
Old lady with bad
abdominal pain.

48
00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:34.886
Somebody's gotta see her.

49
00:01:34.928 --> 00:01:36.387
- Dana. please do me a solid.

50
00:01:36.429 --> 00:01:38.056
- Holiday weekend.

51
00:01:38.098 --> 00:01:39.682
Westbridge is down. and our
waiting room's on overdrive.

52
00:01:39.766 --> 00:01:41.059
I'm sorry. but your charting's
gonna have to wait

53
00:01:41.101 --> 00:01:43.478
until after your shift.

54
00:01:43.561 --> 00:01:44.938
Ogilvie.

55
00:01:45.021 --> 00:01:48.817
Dr. Santos needs you to pick up
a new patient in 13.

56
00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:52.737
- Y-yes. ma'am.
I'm on it.

57
00:01:52.779 --> 00:01:53.988
- Chart while you supervise.

58
00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:55.782
Best I can do.

59
00:01:55.865 --> 00:01:58.868
[both speaking Spanish]

60
00:01:58.952 --> 00:02:01.788
- Setting up a GoFundMe. that's
what her generation does.

61
00:02:01.871 --> 00:02:03.706
That's how they
support each other.

62
00:02:03.790 --> 00:02:04.791
Doctor. tell him.

63
00:02:04.833 --> 00:02:06.376
- Your wife's right.

64
00:02:06.459 --> 00:02:08.711
- Staying here's gonna cost
more than we can afford.

65
00:02:08.795 --> 00:02:10.588
Look. I'm feeling better.

66
00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:12.132
I'll just leave.

67
00:02:12.173 --> 00:02:15.093
- Mr. Diaz. even if your
blood sugar is back to normal.

68
00:02:15.135 --> 00:02:17.011
we have to continue
with the insulin drip

69
00:02:17.095 --> 00:02:18.972
until we clear the ketones
from your bloodstream.

70
00:02:19.013 --> 00:02:21.474
Otherwise. you could experience
electrolyte disorders.

71
00:02:21.558 --> 00:02:22.809
heart and kidney problems--

72
00:02:22.892 --> 00:02:26.354
- Mi amor. your health
is what matters.

73
00:02:26.437 --> 00:02:27.814
- I'll make you a deal.

74
00:02:27.897 --> 00:02:29.649
You agree to stay
on the insulin drip.

75
00:02:29.732 --> 00:02:31.151
and I'll go find
our case manager

76
00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:33.111
to discuss cost-cutting options
for your stay.

77
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:34.487
- Deal.

78
00:02:34.529 --> 00:02:36.739
And I'm sitting here
making sure he doesn't move.

79
00:02:36.823 --> 00:02:38.825
- You should go look for Ana.
- Mm-hmm.

80
00:02:38.908 --> 00:02:39.951
- I can find her.

81
00:02:39.993 --> 00:02:41.619
BRB.

82
00:02:43.746 --> 00:02:44.873
- Hanging vanco.

83
00:02:44.956 --> 00:02:46.457
- What's vanco?

84
00:02:46.499 --> 00:02:48.960
- A really strong antibiotic
to kill skin germs.

85
00:02:49.002 --> 00:02:51.504
- Need a hand?
- No. We got this.

86
00:02:51.546 --> 00:02:53.339
- I'll just observe.

87
00:02:53.381 --> 00:02:54.799
Pretend I'm not even here.

88
00:02:54.841 --> 00:02:58.219
- Let's send off a CBC.
blood cultures. and CMP.

89
00:02:58.303 --> 00:03:01.306
- And also a lactic acid.
CRP. and calcitonin.

90
00:03:01.347 --> 00:03:03.349
- Wait. she's not febrile.
not tachycardic.

91
00:03:03.433 --> 00:03:05.018
No evidence of SIRS.

92
00:03:05.059 --> 00:03:06.978
- Yet.
- What's SIRS?

93
00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:10.690
- Systemic inflammatory
response syndrome.

94
00:03:10.773 --> 00:03:11.774
Sorry.

95
00:03:11.858 --> 00:03:13.443
- An exaggerated
defense response.

96
00:03:13.526 --> 00:03:14.777
- A what?

97
00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:16.863
- Sometimes the human body
can have an overreaction

98
00:03:16.905 --> 00:03:18.740
to an infection.
so we're gonna monitor you

99
00:03:18.823 --> 00:03:20.366
to make sure
that this does not progress.

100
00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:23.161
[phone buzzing]

101
00:03:23.203 --> 00:03:24.579
- It's my boss.

102
00:03:24.662 --> 00:03:26.581
Sorry. I have to take this.
or he's gonna fire me.

103
00:03:26.664 --> 00:03:28.708
- OK.

104
00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:30.210
- Hello.

105
00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:33.880
No. I'm still
at the hospital.

106
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:35.381
Being seen right now.

107
00:03:35.423 --> 00:03:36.674
Ow.

108
00:03:36.716 --> 00:03:39.844
No. they just stuck me
with a needle.

109
00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:41.554
I don't know.

110
00:03:41.596 --> 00:03:43.973
You wanna talk to them?

111
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:47.018
They're kind of busy right now.

112
00:03:47.060 --> 00:03:48.436
I know you are.

113
00:03:48.519 --> 00:03:49.896
- Second IV's in.

114
00:03:49.979 --> 00:03:51.606
- No. I'm not overreacting.

115
00:03:51.689 --> 00:03:53.942
My body's overreacting.

116
00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:55.944
Please--please don't fire me.

117
00:03:56.027 --> 00:03:57.237
I--

118
00:03:57.320 --> 00:03:58.738
- This is
Dr. Michael Robinavitch.

119
00:03:58.780 --> 00:04:00.740
I am the chief
of emergency medicine at PTMC.

120
00:04:00.823 --> 00:04:02.742
If you fire her.
she will sue you.

121
00:04:02.784 --> 00:04:05.745
and I will testify
on her behalf.

122
00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:08.039
OK.

123
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.999
Don't worry about it.
We got you.

124
00:04:14.837 --> 00:04:16.756
- Do you know how long
Jackson's gonna be asleep?

125
00:04:16.798 --> 00:04:19.968
- So there's no exact timeline
with the sedatives we gave him.

126
00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:21.719
but he should be awake soon.

127
00:04:21.761 --> 00:04:23.388
- Have you spoken
to your parents yet?

128
00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:24.973
- Yeah. they're on their way
back from Columbus.

129
00:04:25.056 --> 00:04:27.433
- Maybe you should take
some time for yourself

130
00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:28.893
before they arrive.

131
00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.561
- Yeah. cafeteria's
right down the hall.

132
00:04:30.603 --> 00:04:31.604
Decent grilled cheese.

133
00:04:31.646 --> 00:04:32.730
Stay away from the tuna.

134
00:04:32.772 --> 00:04:34.774
- Thanks. but I'm not hungry.

135
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:37.443
You know. I just can't believe
that a campus security guard

136
00:04:37.527 --> 00:04:38.945
tased my brother.

137
00:04:38.987 --> 00:04:40.446
Aren't they supposed
to be helping students

138
00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:42.532
and protect them.
not shoot at them?

139
00:04:42.615 --> 00:04:44.242
- You have every right
to be upset.

140
00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:46.911
and you should absolutely
pursue accountability.

141
00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:49.163
But right now. we are
taking care of your brother.

142
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:52.000
And you should really
take care of yourself.

143
00:04:52.083 --> 00:04:53.626
- I--I have your number.

144
00:04:53.668 --> 00:04:55.962
I'll text you as soon as
Jackson's LP results get back

145
00:04:56.045 --> 00:04:58.172
or if he wakes up.

146
00:04:58.256 --> 00:04:59.924
- OK.

147
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:01.259
OK. thank you.

148
00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:02.427
- Of course.

149
00:05:02.468 --> 00:05:05.596
- Oh.
- OK.

150
00:05:05.638 --> 00:05:07.223
Hypoactive bowel sounds.

151
00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:10.101
Soft. with moderate tenderness
in the left lower quadrant.

152
00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:13.313
Mrs. Randolph. do you
take Percocet every day?

153
00:05:13.396 --> 00:05:15.273
- No.
- Huh.

154
00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:16.733
And what about your
water intake. 'cause--

155
00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:18.276
- Pause.

156
00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:20.445
Mrs. Randolph. you said you
don't take Percocet every day.

157
00:05:20.486 --> 00:05:22.447
but when was the last time
you took some?

158
00:05:22.488 --> 00:05:25.700
- Maybe three or four times
last week.

159
00:05:25.783 --> 00:05:29.329
Assisted living had
a ballroom dance competition.

160
00:05:29.412 --> 00:05:31.539
and I tweaked my back.
- Mm.

161
00:05:31.622 --> 00:05:35.668
- Any further
questions. Ogilvie?

162
00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:39.339
- When was your last
bowel movement?

163
00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:41.841
- I don't know.
Sometime last week.

164
00:05:41.924 --> 00:05:44.844
I've been stopped up
for at least five or six days.

165
00:05:44.927 --> 00:05:48.348
- Mm-hmm. painkillers
can cause constipation.

166
00:05:48.389 --> 00:05:49.640
- I know.

167
00:05:49.682 --> 00:05:52.185
That's why they put me
on a stool softener.

168
00:05:52.226 --> 00:05:53.519
and then they tried an enema.

169
00:05:53.561 --> 00:05:55.521
- And--and no movements?
- Yep.

170
00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:58.858
And then they gave me
this horrible drink.

171
00:05:58.900 --> 00:06:00.485
- Mag citrate.

172
00:06:00.526 --> 00:06:01.527
- Yeah.

173
00:06:01.569 --> 00:06:03.863
Mag citrate.

174
00:06:03.905 --> 00:06:05.156
Made me puke.

175
00:06:05.198 --> 00:06:07.367
- All right. what's next.
Ogilvie?

176
00:06:07.408 --> 00:06:09.369
- Let's get you an X-ray
and see how we can help you.

177
00:06:09.452 --> 00:06:10.370
Mrs. Randolph.

178
00:06:10.453 --> 00:06:12.288
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

179
00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:14.457
- Differential?

180
00:06:14.540 --> 00:06:16.125
- Probable stool impaction.

181
00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:17.710
But with her history
of cholecystectomy.

182
00:06:17.752 --> 00:06:19.462
it could be
small bowel obstruction.

183
00:06:19.545 --> 00:06:20.546
- Or worse.

184
00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:22.840
- Sigmoid volvulus?

185
00:06:22.882 --> 00:06:25.218
But that's
a surgical emergency.

186
00:06:25.259 --> 00:06:26.719
Wouldn't she have tons of pain?

187
00:06:26.803 --> 00:06:30.306
- Not always. especially when
you're in your 80s.

188
00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:37.480
- I am getting concerned.

189
00:06:37.563 --> 00:06:40.066
This is a millimeter
past the line.

190
00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:41.401
- Or my line was sloppy.

191
00:06:41.484 --> 00:06:42.985
- Any increase in pain?
- Oh.

192
00:06:43.069 --> 00:06:45.571
- OK. sorry.
Let's try four morphine.

193
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:46.906
- White count's only 10.000.

194
00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:48.908
It'd be over 12.000 for SIRS.

195
00:06:48.991 --> 00:06:50.743
- There are other criteria.

196
00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:52.203
- Still afebrile.

197
00:06:52.245 --> 00:06:53.746
- Did you ask about
past history of MRSA?

198
00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:55.581
- Not specifically. but she's
never been hospitalized.

199
00:06:55.623 --> 00:06:57.083
- Any evidence
of an immunocompromised state?

200
00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:58.292
- No. she's healthy.
- Steroid use?

201
00:06:58.376 --> 00:06:59.293
- Never.

202
00:06:59.377 --> 00:07:00.878
- Maximum heart rate's only 89.

203
00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:02.046
- Is that OK?

204
00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:04.090
- That's good. very good.

205
00:07:04.173 --> 00:07:05.091
- Stay with her.

206
00:07:05.174 --> 00:07:06.717
Monitor her closely.

207
00:07:06.759 --> 00:07:08.553
If there's any change in her
condition. come find me.

208
00:07:08.594 --> 00:07:09.762
I mean any change.

209
00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:15.435
- Roxie Hamler. 42.
home hospice patient

210
00:07:15.518 --> 00:07:17.061
with a history of lung cancer.

211
00:07:17.103 --> 00:07:20.273
New-onset tonic-clonic seizure
with right lower leg pain.

212
00:07:20.314 --> 00:07:22.400
- She hit it
on the coffee table.

213
00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:24.026
- [moaning softly]

214
00:07:24.110 --> 00:07:25.820
- Initially nonverbal.
now coming around.

215
00:07:25.903 --> 00:07:27.321
- That's normal
after a seizure.

216
00:07:27.405 --> 00:07:28.948
Hi. I'm Dr. Al-Hashimi.
- Do you need a hand?

217
00:07:28.990 --> 00:07:30.741
- Nope. we got it.
- She hit her head?

218
00:07:30.783 --> 00:07:31.909
- No.
I was there.

219
00:07:31.951 --> 00:07:33.494
I caught her.
- No IV?

220
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:34.787
- Couldn't get one in.

221
00:07:34.871 --> 00:07:36.289
Gave her four of IM versed
for the seizure.

222
00:07:36.372 --> 00:07:37.832
25 of fent for the pain.
- OK.

223
00:07:37.915 --> 00:07:39.750
Dana. where to?
- Trauma One.

224
00:07:39.792 --> 00:07:40.960
- This way.

225
00:07:41.043 --> 00:07:43.296
- Haven't seen you guys
in a hot minute.

226
00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:45.923
- Pickup from SCI Jones Forge.

227
00:07:45.965 --> 00:07:47.425
Was supposed to go
to Westbridge but got

228
00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:48.426
diverted to you.

229
00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:49.802
- Yeah. you and everybody else.

230
00:07:49.886 --> 00:07:51.387
- Princess. I need you
pivot to Central 9.

231
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:52.722
- Got it.

232
00:07:52.805 --> 00:07:54.432
- Gus Varney. 54.
victim of assault

233
00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:55.808
with diffuse blunt trauma.

234
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:57.810
He's got bruising to the face.
the right chest.

235
00:07:57.852 --> 00:07:59.479
10-centimeter laceration
to the left arm.

236
00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:01.022
BP's 136 over 84. pulse 102.

237
00:08:01.105 --> 00:08:03.816
good sats. 95 on room air.

238
00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:05.485
- How you feeling there.
Mr. Varney?

239
00:08:05.568 --> 00:08:06.986
- Fucking hurts.
- Where?

240
00:08:07.069 --> 00:08:09.322
- Everywhere.
- I am Dr. Robby.

241
00:08:09.405 --> 00:08:10.656
This is Dr. Al-Hashimi.

242
00:08:10.698 --> 00:08:12.116
- We'll get you
something for the pain.

243
00:08:12.158 --> 00:08:13.659
- I've got a progressing
cellulitis in Trauma Two.

244
00:08:13.701 --> 00:08:15.286
- Go. I'm good.
- Thank you.

245
00:08:15.328 --> 00:08:17.330
- Gus. do you know
who hurt you?

246
00:08:17.371 --> 00:08:19.999
- One of the fine. upstanding
citizens of cell block 6.

247
00:08:20.041 --> 00:08:22.919
- It's a deep lac
through the muscle fascia.

248
00:08:23.002 --> 00:08:24.462
Can we get the cuffs off
once he settles?

249
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:25.630
- Not a chance.

250
00:08:25.671 --> 00:08:27.548
Orange jumpsuit.
He's cuffed for a reason.

251
00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:29.717
- Let's go.

252
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:37.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

253
00:08:40.061 --> 00:08:43.523
OK. everyone. on my count.

254
00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:45.191
1. 2--

255
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:46.734
- Hold on.

256
00:08:50.321 --> 00:08:53.866
Go.
- 1. 2. 3.

257
00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:55.368
- [groans]
- Mel. E-FAST.

258
00:08:55.409 --> 00:08:56.911
Whitaker. primary assessment.

259
00:08:56.994 --> 00:08:58.246
- On it.

260
00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:04.502
- Oh. weird bruise.

261
00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:05.795
Did he fall on something?

262
00:09:05.878 --> 00:09:07.296
- Footprint. got stomped.

263
00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:09.298
- Jesus.

264
00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:12.218
- Is it--is that necessary?

265
00:09:12.260 --> 00:09:14.387
- Afraid so.

266
00:09:14.428 --> 00:09:17.014
- Airway's patent.

267
00:09:17.056 --> 00:09:19.725
- Good lung sliding
on the left.

268
00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:20.977
- [yells]
- Sorry.

269
00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:22.228
Good on the right. too.

270
00:09:22.311 --> 00:09:23.646
- How are the lungs?

271
00:09:23.729 --> 00:09:24.730
- Good breath sounds.

272
00:09:24.814 --> 00:09:27.525
No crepitus.
- No effusion.

273
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:30.778
- Pulse ox 97. BP 118 over 78.
heart rate 112.

274
00:09:30.861 --> 00:09:32.196
- Tachycardic from the pain.

275
00:09:32.238 --> 00:09:33.739
- Start with four of morphine.
Repeat prn.

276
00:09:33.781 --> 00:09:34.740
- On it.

277
00:09:34.782 --> 00:09:36.867
- OK.
Swollen mandible.

278
00:09:36.909 --> 00:09:38.244
Open your mouth for me. Gus.

279
00:09:38.327 --> 00:09:40.079
Little wider.

280
00:09:40.162 --> 00:09:41.372
- Can't.

281
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:42.748
- Whitaker. you know
the tongue blade exam?

282
00:09:42.790 --> 00:09:44.208
- Yeah.

283
00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:45.626
- It's a great test
for mandible fracture.

284
00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:48.879
- Gus. bite down hard
on this for me.

285
00:09:48.921 --> 00:09:51.090
- [yelling]

286
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:52.425
- Sorry. Gus.

287
00:09:52.508 --> 00:09:54.594
Positive test.
- [groans]

288
00:09:54.635 --> 00:09:56.095
- No free fluid in the belly.

289
00:09:56.178 --> 00:09:57.096
- Any idea how long
this will take?

290
00:09:57.179 --> 00:09:58.472
- Too soon to tell.

291
00:09:58.556 --> 00:09:59.599
Whitaker. your assessment?

292
00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:01.017
- Fractured left mandible.

293
00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:03.185
multiple rib fractures.

294
00:10:03.269 --> 00:10:04.687
Complex forearm lac.

295
00:10:04.770 --> 00:10:06.689
- OK. log roll to the left.
then pan scan.

296
00:10:06.772 --> 00:10:08.608
- Where were you when
Mr. Varney got assaulted?

297
00:10:08.691 --> 00:10:10.234
- I just move 'em.
I don't get to know 'em.

298
00:10:10.276 --> 00:10:11.944
- CT's ready for us.

299
00:10:12.028 --> 00:10:13.779
- Cycling the BP.

300
00:10:13.863 --> 00:10:16.449
- OK. this redness is now
a centimeter over that line.

301
00:10:16.532 --> 00:10:17.950
and this might be
a bulla forming.

302
00:10:18.034 --> 00:10:19.285
- The vanco takes
a little time to work.

303
00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:22.788
- Vital signs are still stable.
122 over 78.

304
00:10:22.872 --> 00:10:23.914
I got it.

305
00:10:23.956 --> 00:10:26.917
- How are you feeling. Debbie?

306
00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:28.586
- I'm feeling
a little warm.

307
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:29.962
- That can happen with vanco.

308
00:10:30.046 --> 00:10:31.964
- Thanks. man.

309
00:10:32.006 --> 00:10:34.967
Lactic acid 4.2.

310
00:10:35.051 --> 00:10:36.802
- OK.
- What's wrong?

311
00:10:36.844 --> 00:10:39.472
- That can be a sign
of a more serious infection.

312
00:10:39.555 --> 00:10:41.140
but the good news is.
we know what to do.

313
00:10:41.182 --> 00:10:44.810
Jesse. 2 liters
of LR wide open.

314
00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:46.312
- This is severe sepsis.

315
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:47.938
- I know. but at 7:00 AM.
it was a simple cellulitis.

316
00:10:47.980 --> 00:10:49.523
Anyone would have
given her Keflex.

317
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:51.525
We could add carbapenem
or Zosyn to broaden

318
00:10:51.609 --> 00:10:52.610
our antibiotic coverage.

319
00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:53.778
- OK. I got it.

320
00:10:53.819 --> 00:10:55.154
Thanks.

321
00:10:55.237 --> 00:10:58.157
Jesse. 1 gram meropenem.
900 milligrams clinda.

322
00:10:58.240 --> 00:11:00.201
and page Dr. Garcia. please.

323
00:11:00.284 --> 00:11:01.661
- What's going on?

324
00:11:01.702 --> 00:11:03.120
- We're adding new antibiotics.

325
00:11:03.162 --> 00:11:04.497
- It's serious?

326
00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:05.748
- We wanna get ahead
of it and make sure

327
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:07.625
it doesn't become serious.

328
00:11:09.251 --> 00:11:10.294
What else can I do?

329
00:11:10.336 --> 00:11:11.462
- I think you've done enough.

330
00:11:11.504 --> 00:11:12.672
You can go.

331
00:11:16.384 --> 00:11:17.343
- All good in there?

332
00:11:17.385 --> 00:11:18.469
- Code sepsis.

333
00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:19.804
Stable for the moment.

334
00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:21.097
How about you?

335
00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:23.474
- Perfect vitals.
E-FAST negative. off to CT.

336
00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:24.684
- Good.

337
00:11:24.725 --> 00:11:26.268
Keep me posted.

338
00:11:26.352 --> 00:11:27.645
- Ditto.

339
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:32.608
- How's it going?

340
00:11:32.692 --> 00:11:34.568
- Great. if you ignore
the hot mess in chairs.

341
00:11:34.652 --> 00:11:36.529
- Any update on our
little baby Jane Doe?

342
00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:38.531
- Security's reviewing
the CCTV from last night

343
00:11:38.572 --> 00:11:39.824
and this morning.

344
00:11:42.159 --> 00:11:43.536
You two kiss and make up yet?

345
00:11:43.619 --> 00:11:45.162
- I think someone needs
to smoke a cigarette.

346
00:11:45.204 --> 00:11:46.539
- I'm trying to quit.

347
00:11:46.622 --> 00:11:48.082
- Why don't you quit
when I'm on my trip?

348
00:11:48.165 --> 00:11:49.375
- Everyone's glad
to have you back.

349
00:11:49.417 --> 00:11:51.919
- Asshole.
- Well. not everyone.

350
00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:55.756
- Hey. you want in
on this betting board?

351
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.718
Look. all you gotta do is
pick why Westbridge went down.

352
00:11:58.801 --> 00:12:00.386
how many of their patients
we're gonna get.

353
00:12:00.428 --> 00:12:02.012
and when they'll
be back in action.

354
00:12:02.054 --> 00:12:04.724
Hey. already up to $500.

355
00:12:04.807 --> 00:12:07.059
- Oh. ah. gotta pass.

356
00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:09.228
Still catching up
on rehab bills.

357
00:12:09.311 --> 00:12:11.814
- Respect.

358
00:12:13.399 --> 00:12:14.483
- All right.

359
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.193
What's the rules
on me changing my bet?

360
00:12:16.235 --> 00:12:18.404
- Only if you double down.

361
00:12:18.446 --> 00:12:20.406
- [chuckles]

362
00:12:20.489 --> 00:12:21.907
Sinkhole.

363
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:27.997
- You watch
too many movies. man.

364
00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:31.083
- Considered the diagnosis
of aortic aneurysm

365
00:12:31.125 --> 00:12:33.335
or dissection. but the
point-of-care ultrasound was--

366
00:12:33.419 --> 00:12:35.921
- You done want that
gridlocked granny?

367
00:12:35.963 --> 00:12:37.798
- Ordered an acute
abdominal series

368
00:12:37.882 --> 00:12:39.091
to rule out obstruction.

369
00:12:39.133 --> 00:12:40.301
Still waiting on the X-rays.
- Great.

370
00:12:40.384 --> 00:12:41.427
Then you're free
to treat our latest

371
00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:42.636
and greatest in South 16.

372
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:45.431
- Oh. come on. D.
it's like. every time

373
00:12:45.514 --> 00:12:47.057
I get a moment to chart.
I barely get

374
00:12:47.099 --> 00:12:49.769
a sentence out before I get--
- Interrupted?

375
00:12:49.810 --> 00:12:51.771
Sucks to be you.
but trust me. it sucks worse

376
00:12:51.854 --> 00:12:53.731
for the poor gal in 16.

377
00:12:53.773 --> 00:12:56.442
- I'm beginning to think
you enjoy torturing me.

378
00:12:56.525 --> 00:12:58.611
- Perks of the job.

379
00:12:58.652 --> 00:12:59.987
- Ogilvie. let's go.

380
00:13:03.574 --> 00:13:06.327
- Hold out your hand. Louie.

381
00:13:07.286 --> 00:13:08.913
A little shaky.

382
00:13:08.954 --> 00:13:09.914
- No surprise.

383
00:13:09.955 --> 00:13:12.082
I've been here since 4:00 AM.

384
00:13:12.124 --> 00:13:13.459
- We can get you
something for that.

385
00:13:13.501 --> 00:13:14.794
- Or I can take care
of it myself

386
00:13:14.835 --> 00:13:16.921
if you cut me loose right now.

387
00:13:16.962 --> 00:13:19.089
- Let's get Louie
50 milligrams of Librium.

388
00:13:19.131 --> 00:13:20.716
- I'll put in the order.

389
00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:25.596
- I will get it from the PDS.

390
00:13:29.141 --> 00:13:31.644
- I'm already assigned
as Louie's treating physician.

391
00:13:31.685 --> 00:13:34.063
Just makes sense
that I put it in.

392
00:13:34.146 --> 00:13:36.232
- Yeah. Yeah. yeah.
Of course.

393
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:43.781
Any changes
with our septic waitress?

394
00:13:43.823 --> 00:13:44.865
- Not yet.

395
00:13:44.949 --> 00:13:45.991
- Wait. if you
have a second. I--

396
00:13:46.033 --> 00:13:47.159
- I don't.

397
00:13:47.201 --> 00:13:48.536
- But the point-of-care
ultrasound

398
00:13:48.619 --> 00:13:49.995
was negative for both.

399
00:13:50.037 --> 00:13:52.373
I considered the diagnosis
of cauda equina syndrome.

400
00:13:52.456 --> 00:13:55.501
- You writing the great
American novel?

401
00:13:55.584 --> 00:13:57.503
- Charting and supervising.

402
00:13:57.545 --> 00:13:58.504
It's Dana's idea.

403
00:13:58.587 --> 00:14:00.047
- Who's the lucky patient?

404
00:14:00.130 --> 00:14:01.966
- Unhoused woman
with a bad cough.

405
00:14:02.007 --> 00:14:03.717
Ogilvie's all over it.

406
00:14:03.801 --> 00:14:05.135
- OK.

407
00:14:05.177 --> 00:14:06.679
- Say "eee."

408
00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:08.389
- Eee.

409
00:14:08.472 --> 00:14:10.182
- OK. deep breath in.

410
00:14:10.224 --> 00:14:12.101
Blow it out real hard.

411
00:14:12.184 --> 00:14:13.853
- You haven't heard
enough already?

412
00:14:13.894 --> 00:14:17.857
- I need to check for wheezing
with forced exhalation.

413
00:14:17.940 --> 00:14:21.026
- [breathes deeply. coughs]

414
00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:23.028
Fucking cough is killing me.

415
00:14:23.070 --> 00:14:24.613
- You smoke. Mrs. Yardley?

416
00:14:24.697 --> 00:14:26.824
- Yeah. but I haven't
been able to

417
00:14:26.866 --> 00:14:28.200
for a couple days
'cause of this cough.

418
00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:30.494
- Mm.
You ever consider quitting?

419
00:14:30.536 --> 00:14:33.998
- You ever considered
minding your own business?

420
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:40.045
- Well. the good news
is that your test from earlier

421
00:14:40.129 --> 00:14:42.256
came back negative for both
COVID and influenza.

422
00:14:42.339 --> 00:14:43.924
but I'm gonna order
a chest X-ray

423
00:14:44.008 --> 00:14:45.509
so that we can see what's
really going on in those lungs.

424
00:14:45.551 --> 00:14:47.511
You got time to let us do that?

425
00:14:48.762 --> 00:14:51.682
- Where the fuck else
you think I gotta be?

426
00:14:51.724 --> 00:14:53.434
- And we're in.

427
00:14:53.517 --> 00:14:55.102
3 grams Keppra
over 10 minutes.

428
00:14:55.185 --> 00:14:56.854
That'll prevent
another seizure.

429
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:57.897
- Thank you.

430
00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.857
Nobody can ever
get an IV in her.

431
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.775
- Yeah. midline cath
is the way to go

432
00:15:01.859 --> 00:15:03.402
when your veins are shot.

433
00:15:03.485 --> 00:15:08.032
- Tachy to 114. BP 94 over 70.
sat 91 on 2 liters.

434
00:15:08.073 --> 00:15:10.743
- OK.
- Cold.

435
00:15:10.784 --> 00:15:14.204
- Is it possible to get her
a blanket and some socks?

436
00:15:14.246 --> 00:15:15.915
- Can do.

437
00:15:15.998 --> 00:15:18.500
- When was she diagnosed?

438
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:20.419
- Seven years ago.

439
00:15:20.502 --> 00:15:23.047
Resected a lobe.

440
00:15:23.088 --> 00:15:25.591
Four cycles of platinum chemo
gave us a couple good years.

441
00:15:25.633 --> 00:15:28.052
but then it spread
to the bones.

442
00:15:28.093 --> 00:15:30.262
- Has she had
radiation therapy?

443
00:15:30.304 --> 00:15:32.723
- Shrunk down the mets.
but they're still there.

444
00:15:32.765 --> 00:15:34.683
- That's why you're
at hospice at home.

445
00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:35.684
- Yep.

446
00:15:35.768 --> 00:15:37.728
- I'm sorry.

447
00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:39.021
- Me too.

448
00:15:39.104 --> 00:15:41.607
- Ah.

449
00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:42.733
- Sorry.

450
00:15:42.775 --> 00:15:44.276
- You have kids?

451
00:15:44.318 --> 00:15:46.737
- Yeah. two boys.

452
00:15:46.779 --> 00:15:48.781
15 and 9.

453
00:15:48.864 --> 00:15:50.407
- My son's 12.

454
00:15:50.449 --> 00:15:52.618
- Goes fast.

455
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:54.453
Too fast.

456
00:15:54.495 --> 00:15:59.083
- Swelling and bruising
over the distal tibia.

457
00:15:59.124 --> 00:16:01.669
- 50 of fentanyl
once her systolic's over 100.

458
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:04.338
- What do you usually
take for pain?

459
00:16:07.299 --> 00:16:10.469
- MS Contin. 30 milligrams
twice a day.

460
00:16:10.511 --> 00:16:12.846
oxycodone for breakthrough.
and sublingual Actiq

461
00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:16.642
for when it gets really bad.

462
00:16:16.725 --> 00:16:17.810
- That's a lot.

463
00:16:17.893 --> 00:16:19.645
- You handle her pain meds?

464
00:16:19.687 --> 00:16:20.729
- Sometimes.

465
00:16:20.813 --> 00:16:22.606
- All the time.

466
00:16:22.648 --> 00:16:25.484
- A hospice nurse comes by
a few times a week.

467
00:16:25.526 --> 00:16:27.820
but I was alone
when she had the seizure.

468
00:16:27.903 --> 00:16:29.822
They told us
that it could happen.

469
00:16:29.863 --> 00:16:31.407
but she couldn't breathe.

470
00:16:31.490 --> 00:16:35.828
And I freaked out.
and I called 911.

471
00:16:35.911 --> 00:16:38.163
- I'm so sorry.

472
00:16:38.205 --> 00:16:40.082
- I'm sorry.

473
00:16:40.165 --> 00:16:42.001
I'm sorry.

474
00:16:51.635 --> 00:16:54.722
- Due to your family income.
you make too much

475
00:16:54.805 --> 00:16:56.640
to be eligible
for either PENNIE

476
00:16:56.682 --> 00:16:59.018
or the hospital's
"charity care."

477
00:16:59.101 --> 00:17:01.186
- But we can't afford
health-care premiums.

478
00:17:01.228 --> 00:17:03.981
- It's unfortunately
very common for people

479
00:17:04.023 --> 00:17:05.232
to fall between the cracks.

480
00:17:05.315 --> 00:17:07.359
It's an imperfect system.

481
00:17:07.443 --> 00:17:09.528
- Can PTMC help
with the costs in any way?

482
00:17:09.611 --> 00:17:12.031
- We can offer
financial assistance.

483
00:17:12.072 --> 00:17:13.866
You'd pay the same
that Medicare

484
00:17:13.907 --> 00:17:15.492
and Medicaid would pay.

485
00:17:15.534 --> 00:17:16.618
- How much is that?

486
00:17:16.702 --> 00:17:20.539
- You pay 60%. we cover 40%.

487
00:17:20.581 --> 00:17:21.874
- Thank you.

488
00:17:21.957 --> 00:17:23.834
Uh-huh.

489
00:17:25.044 --> 00:17:27.046
Where have you been?

490
00:17:27.087 --> 00:17:29.548
- How are you doing?
- I'm sorry. mijita.

491
00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:32.634
You were being thoughtful.
and I just blew up.

492
00:17:32.718 --> 00:17:35.554
- Well. Ms. Noelle was just
telling us that the hospital

493
00:17:35.596 --> 00:17:37.222
is gonna give us
a big discount.

494
00:17:37.306 --> 00:17:39.892
- We can knock 40%
off your final bill.

495
00:17:39.975 --> 00:17:41.894
- That's great.
- Mm-hmm.

496
00:17:41.935 --> 00:17:43.729
- I stay here
for a few days.

497
00:17:43.812 --> 00:17:46.065
my bill could be
over $100.000. right?

498
00:17:47.733 --> 00:17:49.401
- Yes. unfortunately.

499
00:17:49.485 --> 00:17:51.528
It could end up being lower.

500
00:17:51.570 --> 00:17:53.906
depending on your level
of needed care.

501
00:17:53.989 --> 00:17:55.908
- Or higher?

502
00:17:55.991 --> 00:17:59.912
So we would still
have to pay $60.000?

503
00:17:59.953 --> 00:18:01.413
Which we don't have.

504
00:18:01.497 --> 00:18:03.624
- He has to stay here
to get better. right?

505
00:18:03.707 --> 00:18:06.043
- Yes.
- No.

506
00:18:06.085 --> 00:18:07.252
- Excuse me?

507
00:18:07.336 --> 00:18:09.463
- I mean. not necessarily.

508
00:18:09.546 --> 00:18:12.132
Couldn't we just admit him
to med-surg instead of ICU?

509
00:18:12.216 --> 00:18:13.967
Wouldn't that be a lot cheaper?

510
00:18:14.051 --> 00:18:16.095
- Med-surg won't accept him
with an insulin drip.

511
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:17.930
- Usually true.

512
00:18:17.971 --> 00:18:21.600
But let me talk to the charge
nurse upstairs. and I'll--

513
00:18:21.642 --> 00:18:22.768
I'll see what she says.

514
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:24.311
- Thank you.

515
00:18:26.271 --> 00:18:28.273
- Food poisoning in the hall's
asking to leave.

516
00:18:28.315 --> 00:18:30.275
wants to take her kids
to the water park.

517
00:18:30.359 --> 00:18:32.861
- Those places are cesspools.

518
00:18:32.945 --> 00:18:34.363
- Preaching to the choir.

519
00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:35.948
- If she's feeling fine
on Zofran. she's good to go.

520
00:18:36.031 --> 00:18:37.449
- All right.

521
00:18:37.491 --> 00:18:39.368
Louie's in South 15.
Meds are coming down.

522
00:18:39.451 --> 00:18:41.370
Another couple hours of
monitoring. and he can broom.

523
00:18:41.453 --> 00:18:42.621
- Straight to the liquor store.

524
00:18:42.704 --> 00:18:43.789
- Don't pass "go."

525
00:18:43.831 --> 00:18:44.790
- What about
that clamshell case

526
00:18:44.832 --> 00:18:46.250
that went up--anything?

527
00:18:46.291 --> 00:18:48.210
- Out of surgery.
in recovery. still sedated.

528
00:18:48.293 --> 00:18:50.129
- Good.
Keep me posted on that.

529
00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:51.547
- Will do.

530
00:18:53.715 --> 00:18:54.967
- Three times in one day.

531
00:18:55.050 --> 00:18:56.593
To what do we owe the pleasure?

532
00:18:56.635 --> 00:18:58.303
- I came down for a consult

533
00:18:58.345 --> 00:19:00.681
and to persuade Ahmad
to start a new betting board.

534
00:19:00.764 --> 00:19:02.307
- Why. is the Westbridge board
full already?

535
00:19:02.349 --> 00:19:04.309
- Mm-hmm. was gonna ask him
to start one about you

536
00:19:04.393 --> 00:19:06.645
and your midlife crisis trip.

537
00:19:06.687 --> 00:19:08.647
I give it four weeks.

538
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:11.150
Seven. tops.

539
00:19:11.233 --> 00:19:12.442
- Ye of little faith.

540
00:19:12.484 --> 00:19:15.154
- Not about faith. just facts.

541
00:19:15.237 --> 00:19:16.488
- Facts?

542
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:18.365
- Based on my experience.
you're a seven-week-itch

543
00:19:18.448 --> 00:19:19.825
kind of guy.

544
00:19:19.908 --> 00:19:22.077
- Hey. Robby. med student's
got a pickleball player

545
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:23.996
in the North Hall
with possible Achilles rupture.

546
00:19:24.079 --> 00:19:24.997
asking for your opinion.

547
00:19:25.080 --> 00:19:26.623
- Thank you. Perlah.

548
00:19:26.665 --> 00:19:28.792
At least somebody down here
has a little faith in me.

549
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:31.336
- [chuckles]

550
00:19:31.420 --> 00:19:34.089
You know what Motorcycle Mike's
sabbatical is really about?

551
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:36.967
- I never try to guess what's
going on in that head of his.

552
00:19:37.009 --> 00:19:40.179
- Three months being
on the open road by himself.

553
00:19:40.220 --> 00:19:42.347
Man can't stand to be alone
for more than a few hours.

554
00:19:42.389 --> 00:19:45.350
He sleeps with the TV on
in his bedroom.

555
00:19:45.434 --> 00:19:48.270
- I really don't think
I needed to know that.

556
00:19:49.688 --> 00:19:52.816
Look. maybe he's looking
for something new

557
00:19:52.858 --> 00:19:55.694
or trying to outrun
some old ghosts.

558
00:19:55.777 --> 00:19:59.031
- Well. I hope he finds
what he's looking for.

559
00:19:59.072 --> 00:20:01.200
Man deserves some peace.

560
00:20:01.241 --> 00:20:02.534
- Amen.

561
00:20:02.618 --> 00:20:05.204
- I considered the diagnosis
of cauda equina syndrome.

562
00:20:05.287 --> 00:20:07.039
but the motor and sensory exam

563
00:20:07.122 --> 00:20:09.416
were both intact
in the sacral nerve root--

564
00:20:09.499 --> 00:20:10.751
- Our unhoused cougher
has pneumonia.

565
00:20:10.834 --> 00:20:13.670
- I'm cursed.
fucking cursed.

566
00:20:13.712 --> 00:20:15.172
Fuck.

567
00:20:15.214 --> 00:20:16.882
- What?

568
00:20:16.965 --> 00:20:19.343
- That is a cavitary lesion
in the right upper lobe.

569
00:20:19.384 --> 00:20:21.094
Active TB.

570
00:20:21.178 --> 00:20:23.472
What's next?

571
00:20:23.555 --> 00:20:25.057
- AFB stain to confirm.

572
00:20:25.098 --> 00:20:27.559
move her to a negative airflow
room. start her on meds.

573
00:20:27.643 --> 00:20:29.728
- Call infection control
and public health.

574
00:20:29.770 --> 00:20:32.022
And now you get
to sign in as a patient

575
00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:34.483
and get your blood drawn
for a QuantiFERON Gold.

576
00:20:34.566 --> 00:20:36.485
- It's too soon to be positive.

577
00:20:36.568 --> 00:20:37.653
- Yeah. but you were exposed.

578
00:20:37.736 --> 00:20:39.238
You need a baseline test

579
00:20:39.321 --> 00:20:42.491
and then again in eight weeks
to see if you convert.

580
00:20:42.574 --> 00:20:43.825
- And if I do?

581
00:20:43.909 --> 00:20:45.911
- Then meds every day
for three or four months

582
00:20:45.994 --> 00:20:48.830
with regular blood tests
to check for toxicity.

583
00:20:48.914 --> 00:20:50.165
- Jesus.
- All right.

584
00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:51.667
Let Dana know what's up.

585
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:54.753
And for the love of God.
mask up when you move her.

586
00:20:54.795 --> 00:20:58.840
[indistinct announcement
over P.A. system]

587
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:05.430
- Dr. Langdon.
- Hey. man. Alex.

588
00:21:05.472 --> 00:21:06.640
- Let's take a look.

589
00:21:09.226 --> 00:21:12.104
- Ah.

590
00:21:12.187 --> 00:21:13.105
- Is it bad?

591
00:21:13.188 --> 00:21:14.648
- It's not good.

592
00:21:14.731 --> 00:21:17.276
- Sorry. your chart says
you were burned with dry ice?

593
00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:19.319
What happened?
- My jack-off brother.

594
00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:20.946
- Does he not like you?

595
00:21:20.988 --> 00:21:24.574
- I asked him to do it.
just not like this exactly.

596
00:21:24.616 --> 00:21:26.118
- What? Why?

597
00:21:26.201 --> 00:21:27.786
- He was gonna brand me
like I branded him.

598
00:21:27.869 --> 00:21:29.621
- Branded? Like cattle?

599
00:21:29.705 --> 00:21:32.791
- Instead of hot branding.
you stick the iron in dry ice.

600
00:21:32.833 --> 00:21:35.752
let it get super cold. and then
you put it on your skin.

601
00:21:35.794 --> 00:21:37.421
Cool. huh?

602
00:21:37.462 --> 00:21:38.630
- [speaking Tagalog]

603
00:21:38.672 --> 00:21:39.881
- Let's get some LET on this.

604
00:21:39.965 --> 00:21:41.675
I'll get some snips to debride.

605
00:21:44.136 --> 00:21:45.762
- You good?

606
00:21:45.804 --> 00:21:48.098
- Yeah. Yeah. good.

607
00:21:48.140 --> 00:21:49.474
- You sure?

608
00:21:49.558 --> 00:21:52.602
- Doesn't seem like Robby's
all that happy I'm back.

609
00:21:52.644 --> 00:21:55.230
- Well. he's not
going to be here.

610
00:21:55.314 --> 00:21:56.982
and I'm happy you're back.

611
00:21:57.065 --> 00:21:58.984
- Thanks.

612
00:22:03.322 --> 00:22:07.492
- Head and neck CT is negative.
except for mandible fracture.

613
00:22:08.410 --> 00:22:09.703
- OK. let's get him
off the board.

614
00:22:09.786 --> 00:22:10.996
- Roll him. right side up.

615
00:22:11.079 --> 00:22:12.831
- Hey. we're gonna need
the cuffs off.

616
00:22:14.041 --> 00:22:15.792
[handcuffs clatter]

617
00:22:15.834 --> 00:22:18.628
- Ready.
And 1. 2. 3.

618
00:22:18.670 --> 00:22:21.006
- Ah. gentle.
- [groans]

619
00:22:21.048 --> 00:22:22.674
- Dr. King. how are
the chest and belly?

620
00:22:22.716 --> 00:22:25.886
- We have three
anterior rib fractures

621
00:22:25.969 --> 00:22:27.846
and a small
pulmonary contusion.

622
00:22:27.888 --> 00:22:29.097
- Not too bad.
- Mm-mm.

623
00:22:29.181 --> 00:22:30.807
- When do pulmonary
contusions peak?

624
00:22:30.849 --> 00:22:32.184
- After a few hours.

625
00:22:32.267 --> 00:22:33.769
- And do we always admit
for three-rib fractures?

626
00:22:33.852 --> 00:22:35.103
- In the elderly. yes.

627
00:22:35.187 --> 00:22:36.855
but not if a patient
can manage the pain

628
00:22:36.938 --> 00:22:38.857
and doesn't need
supplemental oxygen.

629
00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:40.108
- [groans]

630
00:22:40.192 --> 00:22:41.651
- OK. he's really hurting here.

631
00:22:41.693 --> 00:22:43.320
You think you could set us up
with a serratus anterior

632
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:44.529
field block?
- No problem.

633
00:22:44.571 --> 00:22:46.656
- Oh. as long as that's OK

634
00:22:46.698 --> 00:22:47.824
with Dr. Al-Hashimi.

635
00:22:47.866 --> 00:22:49.951
- If the patient consents.

636
00:22:50.035 --> 00:22:53.830
- Mr. Varney. we wanna give you
a shot to numb your broken ribs

637
00:22:53.872 --> 00:22:54.998
so you can breathe easier.

638
00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:56.208
- Uh-huh.

639
00:22:56.291 --> 00:22:57.876
- OK. get Mr. Varney
prepped and draped.

640
00:22:57.959 --> 00:22:59.503
Dr. Mohan. you're in charge.

641
00:22:59.544 --> 00:23:01.338
- Let's identify the landmarks.

642
00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:02.506
- Cuffs.

643
00:23:03.840 --> 00:23:05.425
Yeah. you can just
leave them off. man.

644
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:08.387
He's clearly not moving
on his own.

645
00:23:08.428 --> 00:23:09.930
- We follow protocol.

646
00:23:10.013 --> 00:23:13.350
for his safety and yours.

647
00:23:13.392 --> 00:23:15.060
[phone buzzing]

648
00:23:15.102 --> 00:23:16.728
- Do you need to get that?
- [groaning]

649
00:23:16.770 --> 00:23:19.564
- Nope.
It's my mom.

650
00:23:19.606 --> 00:23:21.775
Ignore it.
Just ignore it.

651
00:23:21.858 --> 00:23:23.610
- Amen. sister.
- Forearm is numb.

652
00:23:23.693 --> 00:23:24.903
We can irrigate.

653
00:23:24.986 --> 00:23:26.530
- If I ignore a problem
for long enough.

654
00:23:26.571 --> 00:23:28.115
it just goes away. right?

655
00:23:28.198 --> 00:23:30.409
- I wish I could
ignore my deposition.

656
00:23:30.450 --> 00:23:32.661
- That. you can't ignore.

657
00:23:32.744 --> 00:23:33.912
But you'll be fine.

658
00:23:33.954 --> 00:23:35.414
What's up with you. Whitaker?

659
00:23:35.497 --> 00:23:36.915
Trouble in roomie land?

660
00:23:36.998 --> 00:23:38.500
- No. not really.

661
00:23:38.583 --> 00:23:41.753
I think I overstepped
with Dr. Langdon earlier.

662
00:23:41.837 --> 00:23:43.046
- Oh.

663
00:23:43.088 --> 00:23:45.674
- He was trying to prescribe
a patient benzos.

664
00:23:45.757 --> 00:23:48.593
and I told Langdon that
it'd be better if I did it.

665
00:23:48.635 --> 00:23:50.053
- Oof.

666
00:23:50.095 --> 00:23:52.431
- Only because I was already
the assigned physician.

667
00:23:52.472 --> 00:23:54.266
But yeah. now I feel
like an asshole.

668
00:23:54.307 --> 00:23:55.517
- Langdon's fine.

669
00:23:55.600 --> 00:23:57.894
He went to rehab.
he's working the steps.

670
00:23:57.936 --> 00:24:02.441
and hopefully
it's all behind him.

671
00:24:02.482 --> 00:24:04.109
Place the needle in-plane.

672
00:24:04.192 --> 00:24:05.986
superficial
to the serratus anterior.

673
00:24:06.069 --> 00:24:08.280
between it
and the latissimus dorsi.

674
00:24:08.321 --> 00:24:09.614
- Mm-hmm.

675
00:24:09.656 --> 00:24:11.783
- You can see the fluid
dissect and diffuse--

676
00:24:11.825 --> 00:24:13.118
- Dr. Mohan. we need you.

677
00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:14.744
We've got two more rigs
from Westbridge

678
00:24:14.786 --> 00:24:16.955
pulling up right now.

679
00:24:16.997 --> 00:24:18.457
- Go. We got this.

680
00:24:18.498 --> 00:24:19.458
- Thanks.

681
00:24:19.499 --> 00:24:21.960
- How we doing in here?

682
00:24:22.002 --> 00:24:25.589
- Spiked a temp to 102.
gave Tylenol.

683
00:24:25.630 --> 00:24:27.299
Check out her leg.

684
00:24:27.382 --> 00:24:29.259
- That is a definite bulla.

685
00:24:29.301 --> 00:24:30.677
Did surgery come down yet?

686
00:24:30.760 --> 00:24:32.471
- Not yet.
- I need surgery?

687
00:24:32.512 --> 00:24:33.555
- Page them again.

688
00:24:33.638 --> 00:24:35.307
Surgery would be a last resort.

689
00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:37.642
We would like them to come down
and check out your leg

690
00:24:37.726 --> 00:24:40.270
in case we need to remove
this infected skin.

691
00:24:40.312 --> 00:24:41.771
- I thought it was just
a little swelling

692
00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:42.814
'cause I'm on my feet all day.

693
00:24:42.856 --> 00:24:44.649
[monitor beeps]

694
00:24:44.733 --> 00:24:46.610
- BP's down to 85 over 40.

695
00:24:46.651 --> 00:24:48.278
- How much LR is in?
- Full bolus.

696
00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:49.905
- Do another liter
and then start Levophed.

697
00:24:49.988 --> 00:24:51.406
Titrate to a MAP of 65.

698
00:24:51.490 --> 00:24:52.657
[monitor beeps]

699
00:24:52.741 --> 00:24:54.242
- Can someone please
tell me what's going on?

700
00:24:54.326 --> 00:24:55.327
- Pulse ox down to 89.

701
00:24:55.368 --> 00:24:56.828
- 100% non-rebreather.

702
00:24:56.870 --> 00:24:59.831
Sometimes an infection
can cause your blood pressure

703
00:24:59.915 --> 00:25:02.792
to drop and lower the amount
of oxygen in your blood.

704
00:25:02.834 --> 00:25:03.960
- Am I gonna be OK?

705
00:25:04.002 --> 00:25:05.170
- We're doing everything
that we can

706
00:25:05.212 --> 00:25:06.463
to make sure that you are.

707
00:25:06.505 --> 00:25:07.756
Jesse.

708
00:25:10.133 --> 00:25:11.468
- What's up?

709
00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:12.802
- Be ready to intubate
if you need to.

710
00:25:12.844 --> 00:25:14.304
- You want me to call Langdon?
- No.

711
00:25:14.346 --> 00:25:15.847
I will be right back.
and you can call surgery

712
00:25:15.931 --> 00:25:17.557
and tell them to get
their heads out of their asses

713
00:25:17.641 --> 00:25:19.267
and get down here.

714
00:25:27.776 --> 00:25:29.152
Did you bring Langdon
back here?

715
00:25:29.194 --> 00:25:30.862
- No. Al-Hashimi did.

716
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:32.239
You banished him
to scut purgatory.

717
00:25:32.322 --> 00:25:33.406
He did everything
you would've done

718
00:25:33.490 --> 00:25:35.033
with that cellulitis patient.

719
00:25:35.116 --> 00:25:36.535
If you think he missed
something. tell him.

720
00:25:36.618 --> 00:25:38.161
- Well. we're probably
gonna need to intubate.

721
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:39.704
We're definitely
gonna need an ICU bed.

722
00:25:39.788 --> 00:25:40.997
- What happened?

723
00:25:41.039 --> 00:25:43.166
- She is in septic shock.
on pressors.

724
00:25:43.208 --> 00:25:45.001
- Open shoulder dislocation
is back.

725
00:25:45.043 --> 00:25:46.795
- Westbridge shut down
all their ORs. so they told us

726
00:25:46.878 --> 00:25:48.630
to bring them back here.
- You joking?

727
00:25:48.713 --> 00:25:49.631
This ain't the Radisson.

728
00:25:49.714 --> 00:25:50.840
- Not my problem.

729
00:25:50.882 --> 00:25:52.384
Where should we park him?
- Grab a wall.

730
00:25:52.425 --> 00:25:53.802
- Call Noelle. Call ortho.

731
00:25:53.885 --> 00:25:55.053
Call the OR and tell them
we got a patient back

732
00:25:55.136 --> 00:25:56.638
that needs surgery
and admission.

733
00:25:56.721 --> 00:25:58.640
Hey. so sorry
about this ambulance tour

734
00:25:58.723 --> 00:26:00.642
of Allegheny County.
Mr. Billings.

735
00:26:00.725 --> 00:26:02.227
but we got you from here.
I promise.

736
00:26:02.310 --> 00:26:03.645
- Yeah. I'm starving.

737
00:26:03.728 --> 00:26:05.146
Is there any way I can
get something to eat?

738
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:06.940
- Sorry. not before surgery.

739
00:26:07.023 --> 00:26:08.233
- Can I have a visitor?

740
00:26:08.275 --> 00:26:09.734
- Sure.

741
00:26:09.776 --> 00:26:11.528
Any word from Gloria about
what's going on at Westbridge?

742
00:26:11.570 --> 00:26:13.113
- Radio silence
from the ivory tower.

743
00:26:13.196 --> 00:26:14.781
And the charge nurse
over there isn't responding.

744
00:26:14.864 --> 00:26:16.408
- Must be bad.

745
00:26:16.491 --> 00:26:17.784
I wonder if it's something that
security needs to know about.

746
00:26:17.867 --> 00:26:19.286
- I'll keep you posted.

747
00:26:19.369 --> 00:26:21.079
- Hey. you're kind of buds
with Gloria.

748
00:26:21.162 --> 00:26:22.414
Did she say anything
to you about what's

749
00:26:22.455 --> 00:26:24.124
happening at Westbridge?
- No. You?

750
00:26:24.207 --> 00:26:26.710
- Nope.
How are your patients?

751
00:26:26.751 --> 00:26:29.087
- Our prisoner. Gus.
has stable injuries.

752
00:26:29.170 --> 00:26:31.298
and our law student
in Central 10 is awake.

753
00:26:31.381 --> 00:26:33.550
normal LP.
and awaiting a psych consult.

754
00:26:33.592 --> 00:26:34.884
- Good.

755
00:26:34.926 --> 00:26:36.553
Quicker we can treat 'em.
street 'em. move 'em

756
00:26:36.595 --> 00:26:38.013
up the food chain. the better.

757
00:26:38.096 --> 00:26:40.098
- Question.

758
00:26:40.140 --> 00:26:44.352
Why are you treating me
like one of your residents?

759
00:26:44.436 --> 00:26:45.562
- I'm not.

760
00:26:45.604 --> 00:26:47.355
As the attending.
I like to know the status

761
00:26:47.439 --> 00:26:49.107
of all the patients
and doctors in the ED

762
00:26:49.149 --> 00:26:51.401
in case I need
to jump in quickly.

763
00:26:51.443 --> 00:26:52.402
- Makes sense.

764
00:26:52.444 --> 00:26:54.779
Now your turn.

765
00:26:54.863 --> 00:26:56.114
- What?

766
00:26:56.197 --> 00:26:58.283
- As your fellow attending
in our ED.

767
00:26:58.325 --> 00:27:00.076
it only makes sense
for me to know the status

768
00:27:00.118 --> 00:27:02.120
of all the patients
and all the doctors

769
00:27:02.203 --> 00:27:05.707
in case I need to jump in
on a moment's notice.

770
00:27:05.790 --> 00:27:07.250
- Touché.

771
00:27:09.919 --> 00:27:12.464
- You have a non-displaced
fracture. distal tibia.

772
00:27:12.547 --> 00:27:14.633
So if you look at the bone
here. it's pretty well aligned.

773
00:27:14.716 --> 00:27:16.009
- Sorry.
Hi.

774
00:27:16.092 --> 00:27:18.428
Hi. I was in the shower.
and I came as soon

775
00:27:18.470 --> 00:27:19.512
as I got Paul's message.

776
00:27:19.596 --> 00:27:21.139
- Lena?
- Hi.

777
00:27:21.222 --> 00:27:23.016
What happened?

778
00:27:23.099 --> 00:27:24.476
- I had a seizure.

779
00:27:24.559 --> 00:27:26.144
- You load her with Keppra?

780
00:27:26.186 --> 00:27:27.479
- Yeah.

781
00:27:27.562 --> 00:27:29.481
Yeah. she's back
to baseline mental status.

782
00:27:29.564 --> 00:27:31.775
I'm sorry. I'm confused.
Aren't you off duty?

783
00:27:31.816 --> 00:27:34.944
- I'm Roxie's death doula.
- Oh.

784
00:27:34.986 --> 00:27:36.655
- Her--her what?

785
00:27:36.696 --> 00:27:38.657
- I help advocate
for people like Roxie

786
00:27:38.698 --> 00:27:41.660
to make their transition to
death a more peaceful process.

787
00:27:41.701 --> 00:27:44.663
It's like a birth doula
but for the end of life.

788
00:27:44.704 --> 00:27:48.291
- She's been a real lifesaver
for our family.

789
00:27:48.333 --> 00:27:51.127
- My husband cracking jokes
while I'm dying.

790
00:27:51.169 --> 00:27:52.837
See why I married him?

791
00:27:52.921 --> 00:27:54.673
Whatever you have to say
about my condition.

792
00:27:54.756 --> 00:27:56.633
you can share with Lena too.

793
00:27:56.675 --> 00:27:58.593
- We were just
explaining that Roxie

794
00:27:58.677 --> 00:28:01.763
has a pathological fracture
through a metastatic lesion.

795
00:28:01.846 --> 00:28:03.306
- Can you fix that?

796
00:28:03.348 --> 00:28:06.142
- The bones are well aligned.
so she won't need surgery.

797
00:28:06.184 --> 00:28:07.602
- The treatment
is immobilization

798
00:28:07.686 --> 00:28:08.770
and a long leg boot.

799
00:28:08.853 --> 00:28:10.522
- Oh!

800
00:28:10.563 --> 00:28:12.023
- Maybe we up her pain meds.

801
00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:13.566
- Yeah. sure.

802
00:28:13.650 --> 00:28:14.984
We can do that.

803
00:28:15.026 --> 00:28:17.237
- The bones should heal
in about six weeks.

804
00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:19.906
- If I live that long.

805
00:28:21.783 --> 00:28:22.742
- Still numb here?

806
00:28:22.826 --> 00:28:24.369
- Yeah. bro.

807
00:28:24.411 --> 00:28:26.705
- Great.

808
00:28:26.746 --> 00:28:28.540
- You think it's
gonna leave a scar?

809
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:32.585
- I don't think it.
I know it.

810
00:28:32.669 --> 00:28:34.379
- Holy shit.

811
00:28:34.462 --> 00:28:35.922
- Fuck are you doing here?

812
00:28:36.005 --> 00:28:36.923
- I'm sorry. who are you?

813
00:28:37.006 --> 00:28:38.049
- Concerned brother.

814
00:28:38.133 --> 00:28:40.552
- That looks not too bad.

815
00:28:40.635 --> 00:28:41.928
- You gooning me?

816
00:28:42.011 --> 00:28:43.555
- Yeah. it's nasty.

817
00:28:43.638 --> 00:28:45.014
- Thanks to you.

818
00:28:45.056 --> 00:28:46.141
- You did this?

819
00:28:46.224 --> 00:28:47.600
- Oh. yeah.
You wanna see the video?

820
00:28:49.769 --> 00:28:51.688
- Yes.
- Definitely.

821
00:28:51.730 --> 00:28:53.148
- Got you.

822
00:28:54.399 --> 00:28:56.818
All right.
All right. get in close.

823
00:28:56.901 --> 00:28:58.486
- Brothers unite!

824
00:28:58.570 --> 00:29:00.196
- Ooh!
- Ooh!

825
00:29:00.238 --> 00:29:02.031
Dude. why in the world

826
00:29:02.073 --> 00:29:03.658
would you ask to have that
done to you?

827
00:29:03.742 --> 00:29:07.328
- He was trying to brand me
with our family crest.

828
00:29:09.664 --> 00:29:11.833
- Your family crest
is the Penguins logo?

829
00:29:11.916 --> 00:29:13.585
- We were gonna be
bonded for life.

830
00:29:13.668 --> 00:29:15.420
- You already are. with DNA.

831
00:29:15.503 --> 00:29:16.588
- Yeah.

832
00:29:16.671 --> 00:29:18.131
- I love you. man.

833
00:29:18.214 --> 00:29:19.966
I'm real sorry.
- It's OK.

834
00:29:20.049 --> 00:29:23.636
Doc said it's gonna take
some time. but it'll heal OK.

835
00:29:23.720 --> 00:29:25.221
- Awesome.

836
00:29:25.263 --> 00:29:26.973
So maybe we can try again
in a couple of months or--

837
00:29:27.056 --> 00:29:28.516
both: No.

838
00:29:29.934 --> 00:29:31.644
- OK. bag her.

839
00:29:33.646 --> 00:29:35.064
- Yellow on the end-tidal.

840
00:29:35.106 --> 00:29:36.775
- Sorry. got backed up.
- Sounds a little wet.

841
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:37.942
- Someone asked
for a surgical consult?

842
00:29:37.984 --> 00:29:39.152
- That's because all the fluid.

843
00:29:39.235 --> 00:29:40.612
TKO the lines for now.

844
00:29:40.653 --> 00:29:42.947
- Vent settings 50%.
tidal volume 500. AC 12?

845
00:29:42.989 --> 00:29:44.282
- Yep. that's perfect.

846
00:29:44.365 --> 00:29:45.617
- Surgery here.
Hello.

847
00:29:45.700 --> 00:29:47.243
- Hey. it's about time.
Where's Garcia?

848
00:29:47.285 --> 00:29:49.078
- Stuck in the ER.
She sent me down. What you got?

849
00:29:49.120 --> 00:29:50.538
- Septic shock.
respiratory failure.

850
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:52.207
and possible
necrotizing fasciitis.

851
00:29:52.290 --> 00:29:53.958
She needs to go to the OR ASAP.

852
00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:56.211
The infection was isolated
to the dorsum of the foot

853
00:29:56.294 --> 00:29:57.796
five hours ago. but now
we're almost to the knee

854
00:29:57.879 --> 00:29:59.464
with bullae.
crepitus. and edema.

855
00:29:59.547 --> 00:30:01.132
- Yeah.
- You seen nec fasc before?

856
00:30:01.216 --> 00:30:02.383
- In a textbook.

857
00:30:02.467 --> 00:30:04.594
I was a med student
two weeks ago.

858
00:30:04.636 --> 00:30:06.387
[camera shutter snapping]

859
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:08.973
Gotta show this to Dr. Garcia.
- OK. OK. Jesus Christ.

860
00:30:09.015 --> 00:30:10.642
Go get anybody else
from your service down here--

861
00:30:10.683 --> 00:30:11.935
Shamsi. Miller. Walsh--

862
00:30:11.976 --> 00:30:13.061
- I don't know any
of this people. but--

863
00:30:13.144 --> 00:30:14.437
- Don't take this personally.

864
00:30:14.479 --> 00:30:17.482
I just need a fucking grown-up
down here.

865
00:30:17.524 --> 00:30:19.442
- Nice job on the sub-Qs.

866
00:30:19.484 --> 00:30:21.152
Really took the tension
off the wound.

867
00:30:21.236 --> 00:30:22.278
- Thanks.

868
00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:23.947
- I can help
with the skin layer.

869
00:30:23.988 --> 00:30:25.990
Four hands are faster than two.

870
00:30:28.409 --> 00:30:29.786
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

871
00:30:29.828 --> 00:30:32.121
- That just tore
right through the skin.

872
00:30:32.163 --> 00:30:33.456
- You may need to take
bigger bites

873
00:30:33.498 --> 00:30:35.166
farther away
from the wound edges.

874
00:30:35.208 --> 00:30:37.502
- Yep.

875
00:30:37.544 --> 00:30:40.880
Skin seems pretty fragile.

876
00:30:44.968 --> 00:30:46.344
- Oh.

877
00:30:46.427 --> 00:30:48.012
- Yeah. this is not working.

878
00:30:48.096 --> 00:30:50.014
- He has the skin strength
of an 80-year-old.

879
00:30:50.056 --> 00:30:52.183
- Put down Steri-Strips
with benzoin.

880
00:30:52.225 --> 00:30:55.478
not across the wound but along
each wound edge. both sides.

881
00:30:55.520 --> 00:30:57.021
It'll hold the sutures.

882
00:30:57.063 --> 00:31:00.483
- Yup.
- What say you. Dr. Robby?

883
00:31:00.525 --> 00:31:02.443
- Great. MacGyver move.

884
00:31:02.527 --> 00:31:05.363
Go for it.

885
00:31:05.405 --> 00:31:09.117
- Does a Dr. MacGyver
work here?

886
00:31:09.200 --> 00:31:11.619
- I don't know.

887
00:31:11.703 --> 00:31:13.538
- The patient symptoms
are consistent with lumbar

888
00:31:13.621 --> 00:31:17.542
radiculopathy at L4. L5. most
likely due to disc herniation.

889
00:31:17.584 --> 00:31:19.043
- Coughing patient
admitted to isolation

890
00:31:19.085 --> 00:31:21.004
for verified medication
administration

891
00:31:21.045 --> 00:31:22.380
and started on RIPE therapy.

892
00:31:22.422 --> 00:31:23.882
- Yeah. why do I even bother?

893
00:31:23.965 --> 00:31:24.924
Just fail me now.

894
00:31:25.008 --> 00:31:26.092
OK.

895
00:31:26.175 --> 00:31:27.594
Get in touch
with a social worker.

896
00:31:27.677 --> 00:31:29.095
They're gonna wanna
do contact tracing

897
00:31:29.178 --> 00:31:30.930
and help her figure out
transitional housing

898
00:31:31.014 --> 00:31:32.348
for when she's discharged.

899
00:31:32.390 --> 00:31:33.683
- Got it.

900
00:31:33.725 --> 00:31:35.602
- And make sure
infection control responded.

901
00:31:35.685 --> 00:31:37.061
The people in the waiting room
could have been exposed.

902
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:40.398
They need to be
notified and tested.

903
00:31:40.481 --> 00:31:41.691
- OK.

904
00:31:41.733 --> 00:31:44.569
[coughs]
- Relax.

905
00:31:44.652 --> 00:31:46.863
You can take the mask off.
You don't have TB.

906
00:31:46.905 --> 00:31:49.991
At least not yet.

907
00:31:50.074 --> 00:31:52.577
- Oh. great.

908
00:31:52.619 --> 00:31:55.496
This is fucked up.

909
00:31:55.580 --> 00:31:57.749
How are you so calm?

910
00:31:57.832 --> 00:31:59.417
- Expected job hazard.

911
00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:00.710
You get used to it.

912
00:32:00.752 --> 00:32:02.253
- Yeah. no. thanks.

913
00:32:02.337 --> 00:32:04.881
- 70% of doctors in training
at urban hospitals

914
00:32:04.923 --> 00:32:07.216
get exposed to TB
and wind up on meds.

915
00:32:07.258 --> 00:32:09.552
- Jesus.
- Mm-hmm.

916
00:32:09.594 --> 00:32:11.930
- They don't teach you that
in med school.

917
00:32:11.971 --> 00:32:14.098
- Mrs. Randolph's back.

918
00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:15.934
Pulled up her X-ray.

919
00:32:16.017 --> 00:32:17.101
- OK.

920
00:32:17.185 --> 00:32:19.270
No volvulus.
no air fluid levels.

921
00:32:19.312 --> 00:32:21.814
- What do you think of this?

922
00:32:21.898 --> 00:32:23.942
- Fecal material?

923
00:32:23.983 --> 00:32:25.610
- A shit ton.

924
00:32:25.693 --> 00:32:27.278
- Sorry. had to be said.

925
00:32:27.320 --> 00:32:28.821
- So. what. she needs an enema?

926
00:32:28.905 --> 00:32:30.448
- No.
Tried and failed. remember?

927
00:32:30.490 --> 00:32:31.449
- Yeah.

928
00:32:31.491 --> 00:32:33.117
- Time to dig in.

929
00:32:33.159 --> 00:32:34.744
- How are we gonna do that?

930
00:32:34.786 --> 00:32:38.748
- Oh. there is no "we"
in disimpaction.

931
00:32:43.670 --> 00:32:45.838
- I haven't done one before.

932
00:32:45.922 --> 00:32:48.800
Shouldn't I observe first?

933
00:32:48.883 --> 00:32:51.469
- I know just the guy
to teach you.

934
00:33:00.687 --> 00:33:03.481
- I spoke to the charge nurse
in med-surg.

935
00:33:03.523 --> 00:33:04.774
They can take Orlando today.

936
00:33:04.816 --> 00:33:06.567
- Yes!
- That's wonderful.

937
00:33:06.651 --> 00:33:08.152
- They know he's
on an insulin drip?

938
00:33:08.194 --> 00:33:10.655
- They know. and they can
change to a SQUID protocol.

939
00:33:10.738 --> 00:33:11.656
- SQUID?

940
00:33:11.739 --> 00:33:13.449
- Sub-Q insulin in DKA.

941
00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:15.159
- So no IV drip?

942
00:33:15.201 --> 00:33:17.954
- Just shots of short-acting
insulin every four hours prn.

943
00:33:17.996 --> 00:33:21.332
- The med-surg nurses have time
to check a glucose every hour?

944
00:33:21.416 --> 00:33:22.333
- They say so.

945
00:33:22.417 --> 00:33:24.377
And five days on med-surge

946
00:33:24.460 --> 00:33:28.172
is gonna cut your hospital bill
down by 2/3.

947
00:33:28.214 --> 00:33:30.008
- OK.

948
00:33:30.091 --> 00:33:31.884
So what's that gonna cost?

949
00:33:31.968 --> 00:33:33.344
- Well. I can't give you
an exact amount.

950
00:33:33.386 --> 00:33:35.388
but roughly $35.000.

951
00:33:35.471 --> 00:33:38.516
- So after about 40%.
I'll still have to pay.

952
00:33:38.599 --> 00:33:40.351
what. like. 20 grand?

953
00:33:40.435 --> 00:33:42.645
- The hospital can work out
a payment plan.

954
00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:44.355
- Orlando. we'll be OK.

955
00:33:44.397 --> 00:33:45.857
We'll figure it out.

956
00:33:45.940 --> 00:33:48.359
- I'll take on extra shifts
at the coffee shop.

957
00:33:48.401 --> 00:33:51.362
We got you. Dad.

958
00:33:51.404 --> 00:33:54.532
- Let's give you some private
time with your family.

959
00:33:54.615 --> 00:33:57.035
- Thanks.

960
00:33:57.118 --> 00:33:58.703
- Sorry. Thank you.

961
00:33:58.745 --> 00:34:00.288
I was worried he might bail.

962
00:34:00.371 --> 00:34:01.539
- My pleasure.

963
00:34:01.581 --> 00:34:03.207
The real thanks
goes to the newbie here

964
00:34:03.291 --> 00:34:05.001
for thinking
outside the box.

965
00:34:07.712 --> 00:34:09.547
- Sorry I doubted
your med-surg pitch.

966
00:34:09.630 --> 00:34:11.174
- Oh. no sweat.

967
00:34:11.215 --> 00:34:13.384
- How'd you think of that?

968
00:34:13.426 --> 00:34:16.054
- My family had to think
of a lot of creative ways

969
00:34:16.095 --> 00:34:19.057
to help my uninsured grandma.

970
00:34:19.140 --> 00:34:20.641
Leukemia.

971
00:34:20.725 --> 00:34:23.978
System doesn't work for you.
you gotta work the system.

972
00:34:24.062 --> 00:34:26.230
- She survive?

973
00:34:26.272 --> 00:34:28.399
- For a while. till she didn't.

974
00:34:28.483 --> 00:34:30.902
She died before my freshman
year in college.

975
00:34:30.943 --> 00:34:33.237
- Sorry.

976
00:34:33.279 --> 00:34:35.406
- Her death taught me a lot.

977
00:34:35.448 --> 00:34:38.367
Mainly that I don't wanna
be around people dying.

978
00:34:40.203 --> 00:34:42.789
- So they got her. and we
can get out of here soon?

979
00:34:42.872 --> 00:34:44.248
- Yeah.
Oh. I think so.

980
00:34:44.332 --> 00:34:45.708
I think so. yeah.
- OK.

981
00:34:45.750 --> 00:34:48.920
- Hi.

982
00:34:49.003 --> 00:34:51.547
Morphine PCA
looks ready to go.

983
00:34:51.589 --> 00:34:53.549
This should do the trick.

984
00:34:53.591 --> 00:34:54.926
Do you notice a difference?

985
00:34:55.009 --> 00:34:55.927
- Better.

986
00:34:56.010 --> 00:34:58.429
- Oh. great. Great.

987
00:34:58.513 --> 00:35:00.223
- How does this thing work?

988
00:35:00.264 --> 00:35:02.600
- There's a baseline rate
of morphine.

989
00:35:02.683 --> 00:35:04.685
And if you're having pain.
you can push this button.

990
00:35:04.769 --> 00:35:05.686
You'll get some extra.

991
00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:07.021
And you can push
for another dose

992
00:35:07.105 --> 00:35:08.439
every 10 minutes if needed.

993
00:35:08.523 --> 00:35:10.733
- Your very own
morphine butler.

994
00:35:13.277 --> 00:35:14.403
- Amazing.

995
00:35:14.445 --> 00:35:15.947
- She can go home with this?

996
00:35:15.988 --> 00:35:17.448
- Yeah.

997
00:35:17.532 --> 00:35:19.617
Though you'll need
more equipment for the house

998
00:35:19.659 --> 00:35:21.786
now that she can't
bear weight on her leg.

999
00:35:21.869 --> 00:35:23.746
- OK.
Like what?

1000
00:35:23.788 --> 00:35:27.917
- A wheelchair to go to
the bathroom. a shower chair.

1001
00:35:27.959 --> 00:35:30.128
wall bars. if you
don't already have them.

1002
00:35:30.169 --> 00:35:33.256
And a hospital bed
could be helpful too.

1003
00:35:33.297 --> 00:35:34.590
- How do we get all that?

1004
00:35:34.632 --> 00:35:36.467
- You don't.
I do.

1005
00:35:36.509 --> 00:35:38.302
I will get everything
so that the two of you

1006
00:35:38.386 --> 00:35:40.513
can get out of here
and back to the kids.

1007
00:35:40.596 --> 00:35:42.723
At home.
- Thank you.

1008
00:35:49.772 --> 00:35:51.649
- Nice of you to join us.
Huckleberry.

1009
00:35:51.732 --> 00:35:52.984
- What do you need?

1010
00:35:53.025 --> 00:35:54.819
- Some help
with a disimpaction.

1011
00:35:56.654 --> 00:35:58.656
- That is a med student
procedure.

1012
00:35:58.698 --> 00:36:00.074
- Oh. you know the old adage--

1013
00:36:00.158 --> 00:36:02.326
see one. do one. teach one.

1014
00:36:02.368 --> 00:36:04.579
Say hello to teaching
young Ogilvie here.

1015
00:36:04.662 --> 00:36:07.248
- [sighs] OK.

1016
00:36:07.331 --> 00:36:09.333
Double glove. Ogilvie.
- All right.

1017
00:36:09.417 --> 00:36:10.835
Mrs. Randolph.
we're going to need

1018
00:36:10.918 --> 00:36:13.504
to manually unblock
your rectum so that we can

1019
00:36:13.546 --> 00:36:15.006
get your bowels moving again.

1020
00:36:15.047 --> 00:36:16.007
- I know.

1021
00:36:16.048 --> 00:36:18.759
- Here we go.

1022
00:36:18.843 --> 00:36:21.846
Mrs. Randolph.
I would like you to relax

1023
00:36:21.929 --> 00:36:24.807
like you're having
a bowel movement.

1024
00:36:24.849 --> 00:36:27.351
Nice and deep.

1025
00:36:27.435 --> 00:36:29.687
[clears throat] OK.

1026
00:36:29.729 --> 00:36:33.858
Curve the finger
like an ice cream scoop.

1027
00:36:33.941 --> 00:36:38.529
And bring it out.

1028
00:36:38.571 --> 00:36:40.364
You're up. Ogilvie.

1029
00:36:44.619 --> 00:36:46.746
- Some more pressure.
Mrs. Randolph.

1030
00:36:46.829 --> 00:36:48.331
- I'm ready.

1031
00:36:52.460 --> 00:36:55.004
[inhales sharply]

1032
00:36:55.046 --> 00:36:59.091
- And here I thought
you weren't a quick study.

1033
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:01.052
Keep going.

1034
00:37:01.093 --> 00:37:03.221
Mrs. Randolph.
in order to prevent this

1035
00:37:03.304 --> 00:37:04.680
from happening again.
I think you

1036
00:37:04.722 --> 00:37:06.224
need a better stool softener.

1037
00:37:06.307 --> 00:37:07.808
You can try MiraLAX.

1038
00:37:07.892 --> 00:37:10.353
Just a tablespoon with a big
glass of water every morning

1039
00:37:10.394 --> 00:37:11.354
should do the trick.

1040
00:37:11.395 --> 00:37:12.563
- OK.

1041
00:37:12.605 --> 00:37:13.981
[flatulence]

1042
00:37:14.815 --> 00:37:15.733
Oh.

1043
00:37:15.816 --> 00:37:17.360
Sorry.

1044
00:37:17.401 --> 00:37:18.527
- Passing gas is good.

1045
00:37:18.569 --> 00:37:20.238
Means we're making progress.

1046
00:37:20.279 --> 00:37:21.906
- Does that mean that I can--
I can stop?

1047
00:37:21.989 --> 00:37:23.783
- No. Nope.
Keep going.

1048
00:37:26.077 --> 00:37:28.746
[stomach rumbling]

1049
00:37:28.788 --> 00:37:31.958
- OK. Ogilvie. you--
you might wanna--

1050
00:37:32.041 --> 00:37:33.793
- Oh!

1051
00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:37.588
[sighs]

1052
00:37:37.630 --> 00:37:39.173
Much better.

1053
00:37:40.174 --> 00:37:42.093
- MAP's holding on Levophed.

1054
00:37:42.176 --> 00:37:44.095
1 mike per kg per minute.

1055
00:37:44.136 --> 00:37:45.263
- Do me a favor.

1056
00:37:45.346 --> 00:37:46.472
Give me some 4x4s
on some Betadine.

1057
00:37:46.555 --> 00:37:47.765
- Sorry. we're getting killed

1058
00:37:47.848 --> 00:37:49.225
with transfers from Westbridge.

1059
00:37:49.267 --> 00:37:51.394
Mesenteric ischemia.
perforated bowel.

1060
00:37:51.435 --> 00:37:52.395
- Got a hot one here.

1061
00:37:52.436 --> 00:37:53.396
- Yeah.

1062
00:37:53.437 --> 00:37:54.480
Possible nec fasc.

1063
00:37:54.563 --> 00:37:55.898
- Possible?

1064
00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.275
- Need CT with contrast
to confirm.

1065
00:37:57.316 --> 00:37:58.943
- This is spreading
like wildfire.

1066
00:37:59.026 --> 00:38:00.319
By the time you get your CT.
it's gonna be up to her waist.

1067
00:38:00.403 --> 00:38:01.445
She's gonna need
a hemicorporectomy.

1068
00:38:01.487 --> 00:38:02.780
- She needs a CT scan.

1069
00:38:02.822 --> 00:38:05.449
- How about
a stainless steel scan?

1070
00:38:05.491 --> 00:38:07.618
- For Christ's sake.
Robinavitch!

1071
00:38:07.702 --> 00:38:11.122
Robby. what the fuck
are you doing?

1072
00:38:11.163 --> 00:38:12.790
- Oh. God.
I think I might puke.

1073
00:38:12.873 --> 00:38:15.293
- That's called dirty dishwater
exudate without purulence.

1074
00:38:15.334 --> 00:38:17.461
There's a gray appearance
to the fascia. and in the OR.

1075
00:38:17.545 --> 00:38:19.714
you'll see easy separation
in the tissue planes.

1076
00:38:19.797 --> 00:38:21.048
- When do you start
your sabbatical?

1077
00:38:21.132 --> 00:38:22.800
- Tomorrow.
- Not a moment too soon.

1078
00:38:22.842 --> 00:38:24.802
- Thanks for coming down.

1079
00:38:27.972 --> 00:38:31.475
- I'm catching up on my
charting as fast as I can.

1080
00:38:31.559 --> 00:38:34.353
- Why don't you give
my generative AI app a try?

1081
00:38:34.437 --> 00:38:36.856
It's 30% more efficient.
and providers report

1082
00:38:36.939 --> 00:38:38.774
increased job satisfaction.

1083
00:38:38.816 --> 00:38:41.777
And you'll rarely have to stay
overtime to complete charts.

1084
00:38:41.819 --> 00:38:43.487
- Yeah?

1085
00:38:43.571 --> 00:38:44.822
OK.

1086
00:38:44.864 --> 00:38:46.365
Yeah. I'm usually here
at least a couple hours

1087
00:38:46.449 --> 00:38:48.284
after every shift
trying to catch up. so...

1088
00:38:48.326 --> 00:38:50.661
- Sure. AI will make
doctors more efficient.

1089
00:38:50.745 --> 00:38:52.997
but hospitals will expect us
to treat more patients

1090
00:38:53.039 --> 00:38:54.999
without any extra pay.
of course.

1091
00:38:55.041 --> 00:38:56.792
all the while eliminating
staff positions

1092
00:38:56.834 --> 00:38:58.502
for attending and residents.

1093
00:38:58.544 --> 00:39:00.046
- Oh. Dr. Robby.
I am not an advocate

1094
00:39:00.129 --> 00:39:02.173
for erasing my own profession.

1095
00:39:02.256 --> 00:39:05.676
But I am advocating for getting
to spend more time with my son.

1096
00:39:05.760 --> 00:39:08.679
Nothing can replace family.

1097
00:39:08.721 --> 00:39:10.681
What's the status
of your septic patient?

1098
00:39:10.723 --> 00:39:13.476
- Nec fasc.
Surgery's taking her up.

1099
00:39:13.517 --> 00:39:16.020
- Think they'll be able
to save her leg?

1100
00:39:16.062 --> 00:39:17.980
- Right now. I'm just hoping
they can save her life.

1101
00:39:18.022 --> 00:39:20.524
Hey. how's Ogilvie doing?

1102
00:39:20.608 --> 00:39:24.362
- A little TB exposure.
a touch of ass-plosion.

1103
00:39:24.445 --> 00:39:26.530
All in all.
pretty good day so far.

1104
00:39:26.572 --> 00:39:27.823
- Kaison. you came.

1105
00:39:27.865 --> 00:39:29.367
- Hey. ain't no way
I was gonna let you

1106
00:39:29.408 --> 00:39:31.285
miss Peter and Aubrey's
epic Fourth of July party.

1107
00:39:31.369 --> 00:39:33.496
Come on. now. Hey.

1108
00:39:33.537 --> 00:39:35.164
Brought some brew.

1109
00:39:35.206 --> 00:39:36.540
- Oh. you are the man.

1110
00:39:36.582 --> 00:39:38.000
- Appreciate
the bromance over here.

1111
00:39:38.042 --> 00:39:40.336
but no food 'cause you
might go into surgery.

1112
00:39:40.378 --> 00:39:43.005
And no beer 'cause we're
a goddamn hospital.

1113
00:39:46.592 --> 00:39:48.719
- Starting
your sabbatical early?

1114
00:39:48.803 --> 00:39:50.554
- I know someone who could
really use a drink right now.

1115
00:39:50.638 --> 00:39:51.889
- In the hospital?

1116
00:39:51.931 --> 00:39:54.392
- As a parting gift.

1117
00:39:58.396 --> 00:39:59.939
- How's it looking?

1118
00:40:00.022 --> 00:40:01.232
- Good.

1119
00:40:01.273 --> 00:40:03.192
The Steri-Strips did the trick.

1120
00:40:03.234 --> 00:40:04.276
- CT's ready.

1121
00:40:04.360 --> 00:40:05.903
- We already scanned him.

1122
00:40:05.986 --> 00:40:08.322
- Head and neck want thin cuts
and a 3D reconstruction

1123
00:40:08.406 --> 00:40:10.324
of the mandible
before they decide

1124
00:40:10.408 --> 00:40:11.742
if Mr. Varney needs surgery.

1125
00:40:11.826 --> 00:40:13.702
- Have they even come down
to examine him in person?

1126
00:40:13.744 --> 00:40:15.246
- No. they must be backed up.

1127
00:40:15.329 --> 00:40:19.083
- Or there's a July Fourth sale
at the BMW dealership.

1128
00:40:19.125 --> 00:40:20.376
- Labs are back.

1129
00:40:20.418 --> 00:40:22.211
Albumin's low.
Total protein's low.

1130
00:40:22.253 --> 00:40:23.754
He also has
megaloblastic anemia.

1131
00:40:23.838 --> 00:40:25.047
- Malnutrition.
- Probably.

1132
00:40:25.089 --> 00:40:26.215
Jail cuisine.

1133
00:40:26.257 --> 00:40:27.591
Whitaker.
what labs should we add?

1134
00:40:27.633 --> 00:40:29.718
- B12. folate. iron levels.

1135
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:31.220
- Good.

1136
00:40:31.262 --> 00:40:32.847
We're gonna run some more
tests. Mr. Varney.

1137
00:40:32.930 --> 00:40:34.265
Hang in there.

1138
00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:41.272
- I have to pee.

1139
00:40:41.355 --> 00:40:42.773
- There's no PureWick here.

1140
00:40:42.815 --> 00:40:43.983
But here you go. hon.

1141
00:40:44.066 --> 00:40:45.943
I'll help you get on.
- No. No.

1142
00:40:46.026 --> 00:40:48.404
No bedpan.
I can walk to the bathroom.

1143
00:40:48.446 --> 00:40:50.072
I just need a little help.
- Are you sure?

1144
00:40:50.114 --> 00:40:51.115
- I'm here. babe.

1145
00:40:51.198 --> 00:40:52.616
- Oh. we got this Mr. Hamler.

1146
00:40:52.700 --> 00:40:55.911
- You'll have to bring
your IV and portable oxygen.

1147
00:40:55.953 --> 00:40:57.913
- Please?

1148
00:40:57.955 --> 00:41:00.291
- I'll grab a wheelchair.

1149
00:41:00.374 --> 00:41:02.293
- Let's try to sit you up
and dangle your legs.

1150
00:41:02.334 --> 00:41:03.836
- OK.

1151
00:41:06.505 --> 00:41:09.884
1. 2. 3.

1152
00:41:12.636 --> 00:41:15.473
- [gasps. yelps]

1153
00:41:15.556 --> 00:41:17.224
- This is not a good idea.

1154
00:41:17.308 --> 00:41:19.310
- I don't think
we're gonna need this.

1155
00:41:19.393 --> 00:41:20.978
Hey. Paul. Paul.

1156
00:41:21.020 --> 00:41:23.147
why don't you come
grab a cup of coffee with me?

1157
00:41:23.189 --> 00:41:25.107
I'm still zonked
from my all-nighter.

1158
00:41:25.149 --> 00:41:28.777
and I wanna go over some
delivery instructions with you.

1159
00:41:28.819 --> 00:41:31.447
- Sure.

1160
00:41:31.489 --> 00:41:33.324
Rox. you OK?

1161
00:41:33.365 --> 00:41:36.243
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah. It's OK.

1162
00:41:42.917 --> 00:41:44.919
- Bedpan it is.

1163
00:41:46.420 --> 00:41:49.715
[alarm beeping]

1164
00:41:52.885 --> 00:41:54.678
- You lose your pulse ox again.
bud?

1165
00:41:54.762 --> 00:41:57.932
[sustained beep]

1166
00:42:00.309 --> 00:42:01.685
Louie.

1167
00:42:01.727 --> 00:42:03.521
Louie!

1168
00:42:03.604 --> 00:42:06.148
He kept pulling off
his pulse ox.

1169
00:42:06.190 --> 00:42:07.525
- It's on.
It's at 71.

1170
00:42:07.608 --> 00:42:09.068
- Louie. wake up.

1171
00:42:10.653 --> 00:42:12.363
- I'm not getting a carotid.
- I got the airway.

1172
00:42:12.446 --> 00:42:15.533
- Hey. Perlah. crash cart.
intubation tray. please.

1173
00:42:15.616 --> 00:42:18.702
[sustained beep]

1174
00:42:18.786 --> 00:42:21.705
[dramatic music]

1175
00:42:21.789 --> 00:42:28.712
♪ ♪

1175
00:42:29.305 --> 00:43:29.464
